{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/february-digest-2017","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"5cf86cfc-3d43-5089-86a2-f9707bfafe1f","html":"<p>After my <a href=\"/january-digest-2017\">January digest</a>, I got feedback from a precious reader that these stories must be toilet-friendly, so I’ll keep it short, directly to the essence :)</p>\n<h3 id=\"productivity\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#productivity\" aria-label=\"productivity permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Productivity</h3>\n<p>Without a question, the first thing coming to my mind in this month is the set of small changes I made with regards to my typing habits.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/vimium/dbepggeogbaibhgnhhndojpepiihcmeb?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Vimium</a> turned out to be really useful utility in my daily work on my <a href=\"http://shop.lenovo.com/us/en/laptops/thinkpad/x-series-tablet/x220tablet/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">x220t</a>. Together with the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pointing_stick\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">clit mouse</a>, browsing becomes more straight-forward, even when clicking is inevitable. Yes, I feel more comfortable in vim after having vimium in my life, but I still prefer to <a href=\"https://www.toptal.com/php/how-to-be-efficient-in-phpstorm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">be pragmatic at work</a>. In the end, it all comes to wiring up an effective association between the brain and the computer which boils down to having <a href=\"http://www.ratatype.com/learn/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">effective typing habits</a>.</p>\n<p>Another big discovery for me this month was the <a href=\"https://www.imagemagick.org/script/convert.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">imagemagick’s</a> <code class=\"language-text\">[conver](https://www.imagemagick.org/script/convert.php)</code> <a href=\"https://www.imagemagick.org/script/convert.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">cli tools</a>. After spending more than 30 minutes of trying to make a <a href=\"https://twitter.com/kalinchernev/status/835053566632964097\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">screenshot of gmail message for a tweet</a> and not managing to convert paged pdf into a single continuous image, that command in the CLI really did magic:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ convert in.pdf -append out.png</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"graphql\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#graphql\" aria-label=\"graphql permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>GraphQL</h3>\n<p>I managed to spend few hours with this technology this month and I will remember few highlights as a result of that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@kalin.chernev/the-guide-to-learn-graphql-i-wish-i-found-few-months-go-97f9d9ca6f12#.7ss1zopsu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">My short sharing session</a> got more than 1000 visits on day 1, scoring for more than 1.4k at present moment.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://graphql-docs.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">GraphQL docs</a> got published by <a href=\"https://scaphold.io/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Scaphold</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/APIs-guru/graphql-voyager\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">GraphQL voyager</a> got published by <a href=\"https://medium.com/@apis.guru\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">APIs.guru</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The technology is getting further traction and community love.</p>\n<h3 id=\"resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#resources\" aria-label=\"resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Resources</h3>\n<p>Although there have been numerous resources coming by on a daily basis, these are the most prominent to my humble opinion:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://opensource.guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Open source guides</a> by github</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.dev-books.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Dev books</a> summary based on stackoverflow</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Enjoy, and keep reading and writing code for pleasure! :)</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/february-digest-2017","tagSlugs":["/tag/graph-ql/","/tag/java-script/","/tag/productivity/","/tag/vim/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2017-03-01T00:00:00+02:00","description":"On learning new tools.","tags":["GraphQL","JavaScript","Productivity","Vim"],"title":"February digest 2017","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/february-digest-2017"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","3691206191","401334301"]}